A donations page set up by the family of a seasoned sky diver who was seriously injured when he lost control of his parachute has paid for his medical bills and then some.

Ben Cornick, 31, fell 12,000 feet Tuesday without anything to slow his fall but the parked van he landed on at an estimated 40mph. A lack of health insurance led to him paying around $33,000 in medical bills until internet samaritans donated more than enough to help defray the cost.

The donations were made through a Facebook page that has garnered more than 6,800 members and over $80,000 in donations in less than a week.

