The Welsh skydiver's cousin Ricky Davies created a Facebook donations page and reached the fundraising goal within hours.

What happened next was completely unexpected, the page more than doubled its initial target and raised more than enough to pay for the surgery and follow up care.

Even more astonishing, a British physical therapist offered free rehabilitation services for the duration of Mr Cornick's recovery, accroding to a post on the Facebook page.

